diff:1670126632:1670126632:=1,91d0%0a%3c (:if [ authgroup @tas || authgroup @admins || equal {$Author} '' ]:)%0a%3c %0a%3c (:toggle id=gi show="show grading interface" hide="hide grading interface":)%0a%3c %0a%3c >>id=gi%3c%3c%0a%3c %0a%3c [[GradebookArticles.{$Name}|See article in gradebook]] \\%0a%3c [[{$FullName}?action=diff|See all changes to article]] \\%0a%3c [[{$FullName}?action=edit|Edit this page]] \\%0a%3c Status: {GradebookArticles.{$Name}$:Status} %0a%3c %0a%3c (:foxform Site.FoxForms#gradeitem:)%0a%3c %0a%3c (:foxform Site.FoxForms#gradingcomment:)%0a%3c %0a%3c >>%3c%3c%0a%3c %0a%3c ----%0a%3c %0a%3c (:ifend:)%0a%3c %0a%3c [[!{$:Category}]]%0a%3c %0a%3c !Biolinguistics%0a%3c %0a%3c :Author: jaceyagoda%0a%3c %0a%3c '''Summary:''' \\%0a%3c %0a%3c [[#summary]]%0a%3c %0a%3c An overview of how linguistics and biology have merged to become one %0a%3c %0a%3c [[#summaryends]]%0a%3c %0a%3c ----%0a%3c [[#content]]%0a%3c %0a%3c By definition, biolinguistics is the cross study of biology and linguistics. More specifically, the field refers to how language (similar to how humans have evolved over time) develops over time and how human acquisition of language occurs.%0a%3c %0a%3c The biolinguistic approach stems from two main ideologies. The first is about Noam Chomsky's philosophy of "language is innate". The overall disapproval of the philosophy led to the current theory of critical periods of learning which is still the common belief today. %0a%3c %0a%3c The second main origin comes from Charles Darwin's theory of evolution. Most people regard this theory as how species have evolved through moments of time through physical evolutions (for example, giraffes growing to have bigger necks so they could reach leaves off of trees more easily). This caused many bio linguists to wonder how languages factored into this study. %0a%3c %0a%3c Eventually, over time, this origin and perpetual curiosity led to many developments. One of which we use in class is how we 'merge' together phrases in trees. As attempted by Chomsky, the operation provides a basis of phrasal formation as a result of taking two phrases and combining them together. This was one of the many developments that derived from biolinguistics.%0a%3c %0a%3c http://wwwcambridge.org/core/books/new-horizons-in-the-study-of-language-and-mind/introduction/84BBFBBA315DBB3C73547CB405C350FC%0a%3c http://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/S0149763416301221%0a%3c %0a%3c [[#contentends]]%0a%3c ----%0a%3c ----%0a%3c %0a%3c !!Expansions:%0a%3c [[#expansions]]%0a%3c %0a%3c [[#expansionsend]]%0a%3c %0a%3c ----%0a%3c %25red%25 '''Add an expansion:'''%0a%3c %0a%3c (:if [ exists GradebookExpansions.{$Name}-{$Author} || equal {$Author} {$:Author} ] :)%0a%3c %0a%3c (:elseif [ equal {Profiles.{$Author}$:andrewid} '' || equal {Profiles.{$Author}$:section} '' ] :)%0a%3c %0a%3c You must enter your andrew ID and section before submitting an expansion. %0a%3c %0a%3c (:else:)%0a%3c %0a%3c (:foxform Site.FoxForms#newexpansion:)%0a%3c %0a%3c (:ifend:)%0a%3c %0a%3c ----%0a%3c ----%0a%3c %0a%3c !!Comments%0a%3c %0a%3c %0a%3c %0a%3c %0a%3c ----%0a%3c (:if equal {$Author} {$:Author}:)%0a%3c !!Change article category%0a%3c (:foxform Site.FoxForms#changearticlecategory:)%0a%3c (:ifend:)%0a%3c %0a%3c %0a%3c (:Section: C:)%0a%3c (:Category: EndangeredLanguages:)%0a%3c (:Title: Biolinguistics:)%0a\ No newline at end of file%0a
